Colibri iMX8 Linux Yocto Project bring-up
================================================

To get the BSP you need to have `repo` installed.

Install the `repo` utility: (only need to do this once):
--------------------------------------------------------
$: mkdir ~/bin
$: curl http://commondatastorage.googleapis.com/git-repo-downloads/repo  > ~/bin/repo
$: chmod a+x ~/bin/repo
$: PATH=${PATH}:~/bin


Download the Yocto Project Environment into your directory:
-----------------------------------------------------------
$: mkdir fsl-arm-yocto-bsp
$: cd fsl-arm-yocto-bsp
$: repo init -u git://github.com/toradex/imx-manifest.git -b toradex-linux-rocko [-m <manifest>]
$: repo sync

<manifest>                      Description
default.xml                     The latest BSP GA release [1]
                                (this is the default value)

For errors with repo init, remove the .repo directory and run repo init again.

For Colibri iMX8QXP use:
repo init -u git://github.com/toradex/imx-manifest.git -b toradex-linux-rocko -m toradex-4.9.123-2.3.0-8mm_ga.xml

When this succeeded, see README-TORADEX for further instructions.
